The `plugin` group's read/parse surface holds without any plugins installed
(FOUNDATION guarantees, DESIGN §5.1/§5.4/§5.6). These are deterministic on any machine:
they never touch the network or the dev host. As the plugin-management agent fills the
install/enable/disable/search bodies, the "not implemented yet" cases become the real
transcripts; the EXIT CODES, the built-in precedence, and the env-contract routing
asserted here are the frozen contract.

`plugin list` with nothing installed is a friendly empty state (exit 0), not an error.

```
$ RACKABEL_HOME=rk-home-plugin rackabel plugin list
no plugins installed
  install one with `rackabel plugin install OWNER/REPO`,
  or find one with `rackabel plugin search <term>`

```

`plugin which <builtin>` reports the name resolves to the built-in (§5.6). With no
shadowed plugin present it is purely informational and exits 0.

```
$ RACKABEL_HOME=rk-home-plugin rackabel plugin which dev
dev: built-in subcommand

```

`plugin which <unknown>` is an environment error (exit 3, RK0401) — no built-in and no
plugin by that name.

```
$ RACKABEL_HOME=rk-home-plugin rackabel plugin which nope
? 3
error: no plugin named `nope` is installed or on PATH [RK0401]
  help: run `rackabel plugin list`, or `rackabel plugin install OWNER/REPO`
(run `rackabel explain RK0401` for details)

```

An UNKNOWN top-level token routes to the PATH-subcommand catch-all (§5.1); with no
matching `rackabel-<foo>` it is RK0401 — never a panic, never a silent no-op. Built-ins
always win, so this only ever fires for a non-reserved token.

```
$ RACKABEL_HOME=rk-home-plugin rackabel frobnicate --wild
? 3
error: unknown command `frobnicate` (no built-in and no plugin by that name) [RK0401]
  help: run `rackabel --help` for built-ins, `rackabel plugin list` for installed plugins, or `rackabel plugin install OWNER/REPO` to add one
(run `rackabel explain RK0401` for details)

```

A near-miss of a built-in gets a did-you-mean help LINE listing the closest candidate(s)
— never an auto-correct: rackabel never silently runs a command the user didn't type
(§5.1). It is still RK0401 (exit 3), just with a suggestion.

```
$ RACKABEL_HOME=rk-home-plugin rackabel biuld
? 3
error: unknown command `biuld` (no built-in and no plugin by that name) [RK0401]
  help: did you mean: `build`?
        run `rackabel --help` for built-ins, `rackabel plugin list` for installed plugins, or `rackabel plugin install OWNER/REPO` to add one
(run `rackabel explain RK0401` for details)

```

`plugin run <unknown>` (the escape hatch) on a name that resolves to nothing is the same
RK0401 environment error.

```
$ RACKABEL_HOME=rk-home-plugin rackabel plugin run nope
? 3
error: no plugin named `nope` is installed or on PATH [RK0401]
  help: run `rackabel plugin list`, or `rackabel plugin install OWNER/REPO`
(run `rackabel explain RK0401` for details)

```

`plugin install` classifies the source (the frozen, tested part) and then frames the
not-yet-implemented boundary — the install/pin/lock body lands with the 0.4
plugin-management work.

```
$ RACKABEL_HOME=rk-home-plugin rackabel plugin install owner/repo
? 3
error: plugin install for `owner/repo` is not implemented yet [RK0401]
  help: plugin install (release-asset/clone+run, sideload, sha256/commit pinning) lands with the 0.4 plugin-management work; the model + seams are in place
(run `rackabel explain RK0401` for details)

```

A malformed install source is a usage error (exit 2), caught before any work.

```
$ RACKABEL_HOME=rk-home-plugin rackabel plugin install ""
? 2
error: `` is not a valid install source [RK0101]
  help: use OWNER/REPO, a local path, or a .tgz tarball
(run `rackabel explain RK0101` for details)

```
